# .template-removals — paths the CURRENT template version wants gone from an
# instance, applied by `llz upgrade` AFTER `copier update`. copier itself never
# deletes a file the template dropped between versions (it leaves orphans behind),
# so the template declares them here and `llz upgrade` removes them.
#
# FORMAT: one rule per line — `<mode>  <glob>`. Blank lines and `#` comments are
# ignored. Globs are filepath.Match patterns rooted at the instance repo root, so
# `*` matches WITHIN one path segment (it does NOT span '/'). Matching is against
# git-tracked files; each rule is idempotent (a no-op once nothing matches), so
# re-running `llz upgrade` is safe.
#
# MODES:
#   untrack  `git rm --cached` — drop from the index but KEEP on disk. For
#            gitignored, regenerated build artifacts (e.g. the per-env tfvars,
#            which `llz render` rewrites from the spec before every terraform op).
#   delete   `git rm` — remove from the index AND the working tree. For a file the
#            template genuinely no longer ships.
#
# ADD a `delete` rule when you drop a file from the template that instances
# previously committed, so it doesn't orphan on upgrade — verify per file that an
# instance truly no longer needs it before listing it here.

# The per-env <env>.tfvars are now gitignored build artifacts (see
# terraform-iac-bootstrap/.gitignore) — untrack any an instance committed before
# the switch. `llz render` keeps regenerating them; terraform.tfvars.example stays
# tracked (it ends in .example, so `[a-z]*.tfvars` does not match it).
untrack  terraform-iac-bootstrap/*/[a-z]*.tfvars
